<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1151,2004]" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1836,1860]" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[325,682,1836,1860]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossoscolecidae" genus="Martiodrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="huitoto" subGenus="Maipure">
<emphasis box="[325,468,1836,1860]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">Martiodrilus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[488,583,1837,1860]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">Maipure</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[603,682,1836,1860]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">huitoto</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a species closely related to 
<taxonomicName box="[1045,1315,1836,1860]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossoscolecidae" genus="Martiodrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="ecuadoriensis" subGenus="Maipure">
<emphasis box="[1045,1076,1837,1860]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">M.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1095,1140,1837,1860]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">Mp.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1159,1315,1836,1860]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">ecuadoriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Clitellata" family="Glossoscolecidae" genus="Martiodrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="grandis" subGenus="Maipure">
<emphasis box="[1332,1363,1837,1860]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">M.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1382,1419,1837,1860]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">Mp</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[151,236,1872,1896]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">grandis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[251,459,1872,1896]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossoscolecidae" genus="Martiodrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="palmirus" subGenus="Maipure">
<emphasis box="[251,282,1873,1896]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">M.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[298,342,1873,1896]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">Mp.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[359,459,1872,1896]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">palmirus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName box="[521,753,1872,1896]" class="Clitellata" family="Glossoscolecidae" genus="Martiodrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="savanicola" subGenus="Maipure">
<emphasis box="[521,552,1873,1896]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">M.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[568,605,1873,1896]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">Mp</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[629,753,1872,1896]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">savanicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, because of the presence of seven pairs of calciferous glands in segments 
<number box="[289,345,1908,1932]" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" value="10.0" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="7.0">7–13</number>
or 
<number box="[381,440,1908,1932]" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" value="11.0" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="8.0">8–14</number>
. However, it differs in the distance of the setae aa:ab:bc:cd:dd, the placement and number of segments of the clitellum, locations of tubercula pubertatis, the extent of seminal vesicles, shape of spermathecae, and intestine origin (
<tableCitation box="[432,514,1980,2004]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="5.[151,235,362,383]" captionText="TABLE 1. Martiodrilus (Maipure) species with seven pairs of calciferous glands." pageId="5" pageNumber="32">
Table 
<number box="[501,514,1980,2004]" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" value="1.0">1</number>
</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
